article.description: Perry Jones III scored a career-high 25 points and LaceDarius Dunn added 16 as Baylor beat Oklahoma 74-61 Tuesday night.
article.headline: Baylor rolls Oklahoma for 15th home win in row
article.linkText: Baylor rolls Oklahoma for 15th home win in row
article.story: WACO, Texas -- Perry Jones III scored a career-high 25 points and LaceDarius Dunn added 16 as Baylor beat Oklahoma 74-61 Tuesday night for its record 15th straight home victory. Dunn became only the second Baylor player to surpass 2,000 points for a career, while Quincy Acy added 15 points and a game-high eight rebounds for the Bears (12-3, 2-0 Big 12). Steven Pledger led the Sooners (8-8, 0-2) with 17 points, and Cameron Clark added 16. Baylor broke the Ferrell Center record it shared with Oklahoma. The Sooners were 14-0 on the Bears' home court and 26-0 against them in Big 12 play before Baylor swept the series last year. Dunn scored on a drive with 17:07 left to crack the 2,000-point barrier. The senior has 2,009 points, leaving him 180 behind Terry Teagle on the school's all-time list and 247 behind all-time Big 12 leader Andre Emmett of Texas Tech.
